A special election to fill the seat representing [Florida's 6th Congressional District](https://ballotpedia.org/Florida%27s_6th_Congressional_District) in the [U.S. House](https://ballotpedia.org/U.S._House) will be held in 2025. The special election will fill the vacancy left by [Michael Waltz](https://ballotpedia.org/Michael_Waltz) (R), who was selected by [Donald Trump](https://ballotpedia.org/Donald_Trump) (R) to serve as national security advisor in his second presidential term.[[1]](https://ballotpedia.org#cite_note-1)
